The paper discusses the impact of using intelligent personal assistants (IPAs) on language-based primary task performance, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (HCI) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.HCI and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also touches upon cognitive resources, which is related to cybernetics (cs.CYBER) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses interruption timing and relevance, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
